In [3]:
def official_evaluate_metaphor_model(df, tokenizer, model):
    df = df.copy()
    df['sent_id'] = df['id'].str.rsplit('_', n=1).str[0] # I also need sentence ids

    gold_all = []
    pred_all = []

    for _, sent_df in df.groupby('sent_id', sort = False):
        words  = sent_df['word'].tolist()
        gold   = sent_df['label'].astype(int).tolist()

        encoding = tokenizer(words, is_split_into_words = True, return_tensors = 'pt')
        
        with torch.no_grad():
            logits = model(**{k: encoding[k] for k in ['input_ids', 'attention_mask']}).logits
            
        preds_ids = logits.argmax(dim = 2)[0].tolist()

        word_ids = encoding.word_ids(batch_index = 0)
        
        seen, preds, gold_filtered = set(), [], []
        for i, wid in enumerate(word_ids):
            if wid is None or wid in seen:
                continue               
            seen.add(wid)
            preds.append(preds_ids[i])
            gold_filtered.append(gold[wid])

        gold_all.extend(gold_filtered)
        pred_all.extend(preds)

    print("Classification Report for Metaphor Detection:")
    print(classification_report(gold_all, pred_all, digits = 4))
    
    cm = confusion_matrix(gold_all, pred_all)
    plt.figure(figsize = (6, 5))
    sns.heatmap(cm, annot = True, fmt = "d", cmap = "Blues", 
                xticklabels = ["Non-metaphor", "Metaphor"],
                yticklabels = ["Non-metaphor", "Metaphor"])
    plt.xlabel("Predicted label")
    plt.ylabel("True label")
    plt.title("Confusion Matrix for Metaphor Detection")
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

def evaluate_metaphor_model(df, tokenizer, model):
    all_preds = []
    all_labels = []

    for sent_id, sentence_df in df.groupby('sent_id', sort = False):
        words = sentence_df['token_text'].tolist()
        gold_labels = [int(x) for x in sentence_df['FINAL']]

        encoding = tokenizer(words, is_split_into_words = True, return_tensors = "pt")

        # Some inputs are not accepted by the model, I have to filter them out
        model_inputs = {k: v for k, v in encoding.items() if k in ["input_ids", "attention_mask"]}

        with torch.no_grad():
            outputs = model(**model_inputs)

        logits = outputs.logits
        predicted_ids = torch.argmax(logits, dim = 2)[0].tolist()

        word_ids = encoding.word_ids(batch_index = 0)

        aligned_preds = []
        seen_word_ids = set()

        for i, word_id in enumerate(word_ids):
            if word_id is None or word_id in seen_word_ids:
                continue
            seen_word_ids.add(word_id)
            aligned_preds.append(predicted_ids[i])

        all_preds.extend(aligned_preds)
        all_labels.extend(gold_labels)

    print("Classification Report for Metaphor Detection:")
    print(classification_report(all_labels, all_preds, digits = 4))
    
    cm = confusion_matrix(all_labels, all_preds)
    plt.figure(figsize = (6, 5))
    sns.heatmap(cm, annot = True, fmt = "d", cmap = "Blues",
                xticklabels = ["Non-metaphor", "Metaphor"],
                yticklabels = ["Non-metaphor", "Metaphor"])
    plt.xlabel("Predicted label")
    plt.ylabel("True label")
    plt.title("Confusion Matrix for Metaphor Detection")
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

def evaluate_metaphor_model_relevant_POS(df, tokenizer, model):
    all_preds = []
    all_labels = []
    wrong_predictions = []

    # We look only at nouns, verbs, adjectives, and adverbs!
    relevant_pos = {'NOUN', 'VERB', 'ADJ', 'ADV'}

    for sent_id, sentence_df in df.groupby('sent_id', sort = False):
        words = sentence_df['token_text'].tolist()
        gold_labels = [int(x) for x in sentence_df['FINAL']]
        pos_tags = sentence_df['pos'].tolist()

        encoding = tokenizer(words, is_split_into_words = True, return_tensors = "pt")

        # Some inputs are not accepted by the model, I have to filter them out
        model_inputs = {k: v for k, v in encoding.items() if k in ["input_ids", "attention_mask"]}

        with torch.no_grad():
            outputs = model(**model_inputs)

        logits = outputs.logits
        predicted_ids = torch.argmax(logits, dim = 2)[0].tolist()

        word_ids = encoding.word_ids(batch_index = 0)

        aligned_preds = []
        seen_word_ids = set()

        for i, word_id in enumerate(word_ids):
            if word_id is None or word_id in seen_word_ids:
                continue
            seen_word_ids.add(word_id)
            aligned_preds.append(predicted_ids[i])

        # Only adding predictions and labels for relevant POS tokens
        for token, pos, true_label, pred_label in zip(words, pos_tags, gold_labels, aligned_preds):
            if pos in relevant_pos:
                all_preds.append(pred_label)
                all_labels.append(true_label)

                # What was predicted wrong?
                if true_label != pred_label:
                    wrong_predictions.append((sent_id, token, pos, true_label, pred_label))

    print("Classification Report for Metaphor Detection (Relevant POS only):")
    print(classification_report(all_labels, all_preds, digits = 4))
    
    cm = confusion_matrix(all_labels, all_preds)
    plt.figure(figsize = (6, 5))
    sns.heatmap(cm, annot = True, fmt = "d", cmap = "Purples",
                xticklabels = ["Non-metaphor", "Metaphor"],
                yticklabels = ["Non-metaphor", "Metaphor"])
    plt.xlabel("Predicted label")
    plt.ylabel("True label")
    plt.title("Confusion Matrix (Relevant POS only)")
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

    # Printing filtered wrongly predicted tokens
    print("\nWrongly predicted tokens (only NOUN, VERB, ADJ, ADV):")
    for sent_id, token, pos, true_label, pred_label in wrong_predictions:
        print(f"Sentence ID {sent_id} - Token: '{token}' - POS: {pos} - True: {true_label} Predicted: {pred_label}")

# Tokenizing the data
def tokenize(examples):
    return tokenizer(examples["article_text"],
                     truncation = True,
                     max_length = 512,
                     padding = "max_length",
                     return_special_tokens_mask = True)

tokenized_dataset = raw_data.map(tokenize, batched = True, remove_columns = ["article_text"])

# Grouping into blocks
def group_texts(examples):
    ids, mask = sum(examples["input_ids"], []), sum(examples["attention_mask"], [])
    L = (len(ids) // 512) * 512
    return {"input_ids" : [ids [i : i+ 512]  for i in range(0, L, 512)],
            "attention_mask" : [mask[i : i+ 512]  for i in range(0, L, 512)]}

grouped = tokenized_dataset.map(group_texts, batched = True, batch_size = 1).shuffle(seed = 42)
grouped = grouped.remove_columns([c for c in grouped.column_names if c not in {"input_ids", "attention_mask"}])

Initializing token classification model with domain-adapted weights¶

In [17]:
# Loading the data
training_dataset = pd.read_csv("Data/Train Data/VUA_train.csv")
grouped = (training_dataset.groupby("sentence", sort = False)
           .agg(tokens = ("word", list), labels = ("label", list))
           .reset_index())

training_data = Dataset.from_pandas(grouped, preserve_index = False)

# Re-loading the tokenizer and setting label mappings
tokenizer = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained("lwachowiak/Metaphor-Detection-XLMR")

label_list = sorted(training_dataset["label"].unique().tolist())
label_2_id = {v: i for i, v in enumerate(label_list)}
id_2_label = {i: v for i, v in enumerate(label_list)}

# Tokenizing with label alignment
def tokenize_and_align(batch):
    # Forcing tokens/labels to be proper Python lists of strings and ints
    tokens_batch = [list(map(str, seq)) for seq in batch["tokens"]]
    labels_batch = [list(map(int, seq)) for seq in batch["labels"]]

    encodings = tokenizer(tokens_batch,
                          is_split_into_words = True,
                          padding = "max_length",
                          truncation = True,
                          max_length = 512)

    aligned_labels = []
    for i in range(len(encodings["input_ids"])):
        word_ids = encodings.word_ids(batch_index = i)
        label_ids = []
        for w_id in word_ids:
            if w_id is None:
                label_ids.append(-100)
            else:
                label_ids.append(labels_batch[i][w_id])
        aligned_labels.append(label_ids)

    encodings["labels"] = aligned_labels
    return encodings

tokenized_train = training_data.map(tokenize_and_align,
                                    batched = True,
                                    remove_columns = training_data.column_names)
